step.reason:
\begin{align}
3\cos x &+ 2\sin x =t \\
&\implies \dfrac{d}{dt}\left(3\cos x + 2\sin x \right) = 1\\
&\implies \left(-3\sin x +2\cos x\right)\dfrac{dx}{dt} = 1\\
&\implies \left(-3\sin x +2\cos x\right)dx = dt\\
\end{align}

step.tex:
\begin{align}
I &=\int \dfrac{dt}{2t}= \dfrac{1}{2}\int t^{-1}\cdot dt\\
&=\dfrac{1}{2}\cdot 2 t^{-2} +  C =  \dfrac{1}{t^{2}} +C\\
&= \dfrac{1}{\left(3\cos x + 2\sin x\right)^2} +C\\
\end{align}
